The Events Calendar and Event Tickets 4.3.4.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"George\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1696:\"<p>We’ve just released an update to The Events Calendar and Event Tickets to address an issue that some folks encountered after updating to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-events-calendar-4-3-4-event-tickets-4-3-4-premium-plugins/\" target=\"_blank\">the Maintenance Release we just released yesterday</a>.</p>\n<p>The issue is that there were two stray characters left in a main PHP file for both plugins. This may <em>sound</eM> innocuous, but could cause a number of issues of varying severity, so it&#8217;s important that we publish a correction of that mistake.</p>\n<p><strong>The only plugins affected by this release are The Events Calendar and Event Tickets</strong>, specifically, <strong>which are now at version 4.3.4.1</strong>. To learn about the status of other plugins at this time, please consult our Maintenance Release notes from yesterday <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-events-calendar-4-3-4-event-tickets-4-3-4-premium-plugins/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2/72x72/1f4e3.png\" alt=\"📣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> <strong>Enormous thanks</strong> to user <a href=\"https://github.com/Aetles\" target=\"_blank\">Adrian Bengtson</a>, who not only reported the issue but also submitted a Pull Request on GitHub that fixed the code. Thanks, Adrian!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hotfix-release-events-calendar-event-tickets-4-3-4-1/\">Hotfix Release: The Events Calendar and Event Tickets 4.3.4.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"Maintenance Release: The Events Calendar 4.3.4, Event Tickets 4.3.4, and Premium Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:108:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-events-calendar-4-3-4-event-tickets-4-3-4-premium-plugins/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 08 Dec 2016 21:06:35 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1202576\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:720:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the fourth Maintenance Release of the 4.3 release cycle. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. This maintenance release is fairly limited in scope, as a major Feature Release is just around the corner—stay tuned to&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-events-calendar-4-3-4-event-tickets-4-3-4-premium-plugins/\">Maintenance Release: The Events Calendar 4.3.4, Event Tickets 4.3.4, and Premium Plugins</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"George\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3217:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the fourth Maintenance Release of the 4.3 release cycle. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>This maintenance release is fairly limited in scope, as a major Feature Release is just around the corner—stay tuned to this blog or <a href=\"https://confirmsubscription.com/h/r/F35BA2B75B521339\" target=\"_blank\">subscribe to our newsletter</a> to learn when the next Feature Release is live!</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.3.4</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.3.4</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.3.4</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#eb\">Eventbrite Tickets 4.3.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.3.4</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Tribe Common is now loaded only once across our plugin suite, which improves performance in some cases</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> (Event Aggregator) — Fixed an issue where Facebook featured images would not be set on import</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> (Event Aggregator) — Google Calendar and iCalendar files are now updating their respective events</li>\n<p>	<!--\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> (Event Aggregator) — On-demand Event Aggregator records will update events correctly</li>\n\n-->\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.3.4</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Tribe Common is now loaded only once across our plugin suite, which improves performance in some cases</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.3.4</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fieldset admin menu now shows correctly when only Event Tickets is active</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"eb\">Eventbrite Tickets 4.3.2</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Resolved issue where bad website data was added to Organizers when syncing to Eventbrite without Events Calendar PRO active.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Events Calendar Pro 4.3.3</li>\n<li>Filter Bar 4.3.3</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.3.1</li>\n<li>Community Events 4.3.1</li>\n<li>Community Tickets 4.3.1</li>\n<li>GigPress 2.3.17</li>\n<li>iCal Importer 4.2.5 (<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/moving-to-event-aggregator/\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a>)</li>\n<li>Facebook Importer 4.2.5 (<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/moving-to-event-aggregator/\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-events-calendar-4-3-4-event-tickets-4-3-4-premium-plugins/\">Maintenance Release: The Events Calendar 4.3.4, Event Tickets 4.3.4, and Premium Plugins</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"Expired: Black Friday Sale\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/sale-black-friday-2016/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 22 Nov 2016 14:00:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Promotion\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1192977\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:579:\"<p>For current promotions, check out our deals page.  Thanksgiving is just around the corner, which means we can guess with 99.8% certainty you&#8217;ve already been bombarded by all kinds of Black Friday and Cyber Monday deals. Spoiler Alert &#8211; We&#8217;re doing one too. But we&#8217;re doing it our way. We want you to have plenty of&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/sale-black-friday-2016/\">Expired: Black Friday Sale</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Jen Jamar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9065:\"<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1195163\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/ECP_BlackFriday_saveupto30_3.jpg\" alt=\"Black Friday Save up to 30%\" width=\"100%\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>For current promotions, <a href=\"http://m.tri.be/19jc\">check out our deals page</a>. </strong></em></p>\n<p>Thanksgiving is just around the corner, which means we can guess with 99.8% certainty you&#8217;ve already been bombarded by all kinds of Black Friday and Cyber Monday deals.</p>\n<p><strong>Spoiler Alert</strong> &#8211; We&#8217;re doing one too. But we&#8217;re doing it our way.</p>\n<p>We want you to have plenty of time to spend with your family, cook your tofurkey, and watch sportsball with your friends this week. Or any other things you might want to do instead.</p>\n<p>So whenever you&#8217;re ready to fire up your screen &amp; do some plugin shopping, these sweet deals will be right here waiting for you.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><del>Spend up to $149 and save 10% with code: <b>Rest</b></del></li>\n<li><del>Spend $150-$299 and save 15% with code: <strong>Relaxation</strong></del></li>\n<li><del>Spend $300+ and save 30% with code: <b>Rejuvenation</b></del></li>\n</ul>\n<p><del>Go ahead and use these codes anytime between now and Monday, November 28th. Though you can&#8217;t combine them with other promotions, renewals, or bundle discounts, you can use them for ANY of our license levels &#8211; including unlimited!</del></p>\n<h2>Start Shopping Now</h2>\n<div class=\"pbc-products\" data-style=\"display: flex;\">\n<div class=\"pbc-product\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/\"><br />\n</a></p>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-icon\" style=\"background: url(\'https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2013/02/ecp_cover1-300x300.jpg\'); background-size: cover;\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2013/02/ECP.svg\" alt=\"Events Calendar PRO\" width=\"157\" height=\"150\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-content-wrap\">\n<h5><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Events Calendar PRO</a></h5>\n<p>Add advanced calendar features including recurring events, new views, customizable widgets, custom event attributes, location search, and much more.<br />\n<a class=\"learn-more\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Learn More »</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets-plus/\"><br />\n</a></p>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-icon\" style=\"background: url(\'https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2015/12/banner-tickets-pro-2000x705-2-300x300.jpg\'); background-size: cover;\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets-plus/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2015/12/ticketsplus.svg\" alt=\"Event Tickets Plus\" width=\"220\" height=\"150\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-content-wrap\">\n<h5><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets-plus/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Event Tickets Plus</a></h5>\n<p>Start selling tickets today! Using your favorite eCommerce engine, you can sell tickets, manage attendees, and run reports all from within your WordPress dashboard.<br />\n<a class=\"learn-more\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets-plus/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Learn More »</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-filterbar/\"><br />\n</a></p>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-icon\" style=\"background: url(\'https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2014/12/banner_filters2-300x300.jpg\'); background-size: cover;\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-filterbar/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2013/07/filter.svg\" alt=\"Filter Bar\" width=\"214\" height=\"150\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-content-wrap\">\n<h5><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-filterbar/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Filter Bar</a></h5>\n<p>Add a configurable set of filters to your event pages so users can find the exact events that interest them. Works with The Events Calendar and Events Calendar PRO.<br />\n<a class=\"learn-more\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-filterbar/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Learn More »</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/event-aggregator/\"><br />\n</a></p>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-icon\" style=\"background: url(\'https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/09/event-aggregator.jpg\'); background-size: cover;\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/event-aggregator/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/09/aggregator-1.svg\" alt=\"Event Aggregator\" width=\"157\" height=\"150\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-content-wrap\">\n<h5><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/event-aggregator/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Event Aggregator</a></h5>\n<p>Effortlessly fill your calendar with events from Facebook, Meetup, Google Calendar, iCalendar, CSV, and ICS. Import manually or set up automatic imports to run on a schedule.<br />\n<a class=\"learn-more\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/event-aggregator/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Learn More »</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/\"><br />\n</a></p>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-icon\" style=\"background: url(\'https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2014/10/banner_community4-300x300.jpg\'); background-size: cover;\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2015/11/community.svg\" alt=\"Community Events\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-content-wrap\">\n<h5><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Community Events</a></h5>\n<p>Let users add their own events directly to your calendar. With front-end event submission, they&#8217;ll never have to touch your admin and you can choose to review before publishing.<br />\n<a class=\"learn-more\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Learn More »</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-eventbrite-tickets/\"><br />\n</a></p>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-icon\" style=\"background: url(\'https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2014/10/banner_eb-300x300.jpg\'); background-size: cover;\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-eventbrite-tickets/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2013/02/eventbrite-2.svg\" alt=\"Eventbrite Tickets\" width=\"220\" height=\"150\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"pbc-product-content-wrap\">\n<h5><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-eventbrite-tickets/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Eventbrite Tickets</a></h5>\n<p>Sell tickets on your WordPress site by connecting to your Eventbrite.com account. Import/export between WordPress and Eventbrite to easily incorporate ticket sales into your calendar.<br />\n<a class=\"learn-more\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-eventbrite-tickets/?utm_source=tec-website&amp;utm_campaign=2016blackfriday&amp;utm_medium=blog-post\">Learn More »</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/sale-black-friday-2016/\">Expired: Black Friday Sale</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"Maintenance Release: The Events Calendar 4.3.3, Event Tickets 4.3.3, and Premium Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:108:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-events-calendar-4-3-3-event-tickets-4-3-3-premium-plugins/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 16 Nov 2016 16:49:23 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Products\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Release Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1192904\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:718:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the third Maintenance Release of the 4.3 release cycle. Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below: The&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-events-calendar-4-3-3-event-tickets-4-3-3-premium-plugins/\">Maintenance Release: The Events Calendar 4.3.3, Event Tickets 4.3.3, and Premium Plugins</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"George\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4757:\"<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the third Maintenance Release of the 4.3 release cycle. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\">Maintenance Releases</a> are smaller updates between major updates that are mostly comprised of bug fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements.</p>\n<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#tec\">The Events Calendar 4.3.3</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecp\">Events Calendar Pro 4.3.3</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#fb\">Filter Bar 4.3.3</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#et\">Event Tickets 4.3.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.3.2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"tec\">The Events Calendar 4.3.3</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> — Added Tribe Extension class and loader to make small add-ons easier to build.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ordering of events on Month View days is working as expected again.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Enable ampersand character in mobile Month View titles (thanks @kate for the report of this).</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevent erroneous notices for Event Aggregator license checking.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Mismatched text domains are resolved; important for translations (props to @Hans).</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Sticky on Month View is working as expect again.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevent HTTPS websites from attempting to load plugin assets over HTTP.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — On <kbd>WP_Query</kbd> we no longer overwrite custom <kbd>post__not_in</kbd> params.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"ecp\">Events Calendar Pro 4.3.3</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fresh installs now have fully functional Week, Photo, and Map View permalinks.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — The category filter on the <kbd>[tribe_events]</kbd> shortcode is now fully functional.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Widgets selector for term filtering is working again for new widgets.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Resolve issues with private recurring events&#8217; sample permalinks and visibility for their /all/ pages (thanks @brian for reporting this one in the forums).</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Ensure support for the ampersand character in mobile Week View titles (thanks @kate for this report).</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"fb\">Filter Bar 4.3.3</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Vertical layout for filters is working as expected, not expanding to 100% width anymore.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Fixed an issue where Private Browsing on Safari (both OSX and iOS) would cause JavaScript fatal errors.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"et\">Event Tickets 4.3.3</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> — Added Tribe Extension class and loader to make small add-ons easier to build.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> — Prevent HTTPS websites from attempting to load plugin assets over HTTP.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"etp\">Event Tickets Plus 4.3.3</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Included a new filter <kbd>tribe_events_tickets_woo_get_ticket</kbd> for better ticket control on WooCommerce (props to @helgatheviking).</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Included a new filter <kbd>tribe_events_tickets_edd_get_ticket</kbd> for better ticket control on EDD (props to @helgatheviking).</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Included a new filter <kbd>tribe_events_tickets_shopp_get_ticket</kbd> for better ticket control on Shopp (props to @helgatheviking).</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> — Included a new filter <kbd>tribe_events_tickets_wpec_get_ticket</kbd> for better ticket control on WPEC (props to @helgatheviking).</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h3 id=\"not-updated\">Not Updated This Release</h3>\n<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.3.1</li>\n<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.3.1</li>\n<li>Community Events 4.3.1</li>\n<li>Community Tickets 4.3.1</li>\n<li>GigPress 2.3.17</li>\n<li>iCal Importer 4.2.5 (<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/moving-to-event-aggregator/\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a>)</li>\n<li>Facebook Importer 4.2.5 (<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/moving-to-event-aggregator/\" target=\"_blank\">read more</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-events-calendar-4-3-3-event-tickets-4-3-3-premium-plugins/\">Maintenance Release: The Events Calendar 4.3.3, Event Tickets 4.3.3, and Premium Plugins</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"How Total Strangers Helped Us Reach Our Biggest Milestone Yet\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/5-million-downloads/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 14 Nov 2016 18:07:08 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1188665\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:629:\"<p>Last week we reached our biggest milestone yet for The Events Calendar, our flagship WordPress plugin &#8211; 5 million downloads! It&#8217;s crazy to realize just how far we&#8217;ve come. At this very moment, hundreds of thousands of users are running our plugins on their site. Some of those users are people we&#8217;ve met, either in-person or online,&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/5-million-downloads/\">How Total Strangers Helped Us Reach Our Biggest Milestone Yet</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Jen Jamar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5349:\"<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1209007\" src=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200.png\" alt=\"The Events Calendar celebrates 5 million downloads\" width=\"1200\" height=\"628\" srcset=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200.png 1200w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-140x73.png 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-300x157.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-768x402.png 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-665x348.png 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-430x225.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-645x338.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-1068x559.png 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-460x241.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-600x314.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2016/11/5million1200-500x262.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /></p>\n<p>Last week we reached our biggest milestone yet for <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar/\">The Events Calendar</a>, our flagship WordPress plugin &#8211; 5 million downloads!</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s crazy to realize just how far we&#8217;ve come. At this very moment, hundreds of thousands of users are running our plugins on their site. Some of those users are people we&#8217;ve met, either in-person or online, but most of them are total strangers that put their trust in our code based on the reputation we&#8217;ve built for our company over the past decade.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re incredibly humbled, to say the least. We realize this kind of growth doesn&#8217;t happen in a vacuum, and we&#8217;ve got a lot of folks to thank that have helped us reach this milestone.</p>\n<h2>Our Thanks to You</h2>\n<p>You (yes you) are the reason we do what we do. Every time you download one of our free plugins or purchase a premium add-on, you support our continued investment in the development and longevity of our products. When you vote on a new feature request or leave us a review, it helps us determine where to put our efforts next.</p>\n<h2>Our Thanks to Our Team</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/the-team/\">We couldn&#8217;t ask for a better team</a> to support and grow our suite of event management and ticketing plugins.</p>\n<p>Our support team includes the front-line folks you see every day in the support forums troubleshooting issues, offering advice, and making sure you get the most out of our plugins and services. They embody our values of being happy, helpful, curious, and accountable, and we very much appreciate how well they support our users.</p>\n<p>We also want to thank the folks that aren&#8217;t in the spotlight, but are still hugely important to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar/\">The Events Calendar</a>, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets</a>, and all of our premium add-ons. Our developers, designers, QA analysts, strategists, and project managers run things behind-the-scenes, making sure we maintain our schedule of frequent maintenance releases and build new features that maximize value for our users.</p>\n<p><em>Want to join our merry band of pixel makers and help us reach our next milestone? <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/join-our-team/\">We&#8217;re hiring.</a> </em></p>\n<h2>So What&#8217;s Next?</h2>\n<p>Hitting 5 million downloads is amazing, but we&#8217;ve still got plenty of room to innovate, improve, and grow.</p>\n<p>Even with such a large user base, we&#8217;re still committed to reading and replying to every single review we receive on WordPress.org so we can find opportunities for improvement. In our premium forums, we use an end-of-thread rating system to get feedback on our customer support. We also regularly review User Voice suggestions to see what new features people would like us to add to our existing plugins.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve already got some big things planned for 2017 and beyond, as well as several ideas that are still being fleshed out. That&#8217;s where you come in &#8211; we want to get to know you better so we can develop plugins and services that make your WordPress site even better.</p>\n<h2>2016 User Survey + iPad Air Giveaway</h2>\n<p>While we&#8217;d love to take you out to coffee and hear your comments first-hand, with as many users as we have, that just isn&#8217;t practical.</p>\n<p>Instead, we&#8217;re asking you to share your feedback via <strong><a href=\"http://moderntribeinc.polldaddy.com/s/2016-user-survey\">our 2016 User Survey</a>.</strong> As our thanks for your time, everyone that completes the survey will be entered into our iPad Air 2 giveaway.</p>\n<p>The survey takes about 10-15 minutes and can be completed anonymously if you prefer.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/5-million-downloads/\">How Total Strangers Helped Us Reach Our Biggest Milestone Yet</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"Holiday Calendar Maintenance Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/holiday-calendar-maintenance-tips/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 09 Nov 2016 22:52:46 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Articles\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"maintenance\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1189930\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:631:\"<p>The holiday season is jam-packed with events, which means your site&#8217;s calendar is about to get extra busy. To help you prepare your WordPress site for higher traffic volumes, we&#8217;ve pulled together some helpful housekeeping tips. Holiday Calendar Maintenance Tips Backup Your Site Hopefully, you&#8217;re already doing this regularly. If not, do it now. The rest&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/holiday-calendar-maintenance-tips/\">Holiday Calendar Maintenance Tips</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Jen Jamar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7362:\"<p>The holiday season is jam-packed with events, which means your site&#8217;s calendar is about to get extra busy. To help you prepare your WordPress site for higher traffic volumes, we&#8217;ve pulled together some helpful housekeeping tips.</p>\n<h2>Holiday Calendar Maintenance Tips</h2>\n<h3>Backup Your Site</h3>\n<p>Hopefully, you&#8217;re already doing this regularly. If not, do it now. The rest of this post can wait. (Really, it&#8217;s THAT important.)</p>\n<p>In the event something goes wrong over the holidays, a complete backup of your site will help ensure you&#8217;re able to get back up &amp; running so you don&#8217;t miss out on traffic or sales.</p>\n<p>There are a few different options to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/options-to-create-a-wordpress-backup-database/\">create a backup database</a>. No matter which you choose, you&#8217;ll want to follow the rule of thumb to keep more than one backup, each stored in a different location. This way, if one backup file is compromised, you still have an alternate to use if you need to restore your site.</p>\n<h3>Make Sure Plugins &amp; Themes Are Up To Date</h3>\n<p>In addition to updates for WordPress itself, it&#8217;s important to keep your plugins and themes up-to-date. Updates provide important security and functionality improvements, so it&#8217;s recommended you always run the current version available for your plugins and themes.</p>\n<p>There are two ways to keep track of available updates:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/automatic-updates/\">Automatic Update Alerts</a> &#8211; Notifies you of available updates within your WordPress dashboard</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/manual-updates/\">Manual Updates</a> &#8211; Useful when your server configuration doesn&#8217;t allow automatic updates</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That said, not all updates are created equal and there is always a chance an update could cause something to go wonky on your site. For this reason, it&#8217;s important to test updates on a development or staging site before rolling them out to your live site.</p>\n<h3>Find &amp; Fix 404 Errors</h3>\n<p>Users and Google alike are disappointed when they hit broken links on your site. Google and Bing both provide free tools to check your site for errors.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/webmasters/tools/home\">Google Search Console</a> &gt; Crawl &gt; Crawl Errors</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.bing.com/toolbox/webmaster\">Bing Webmaster Tools</a> &gt; Reports &amp; Data &gt; Crawl Information</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you&#8217;re seeing errors specific to your event listings, we&#8217;ve got a <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/fixing-http-404-errors/\">handy knowledgebase guide</a> to help you fix HTTP 404 errors. For more detailed instructions on fixing 404 errors, including ways to search for broken images on your site, check out <a href=\"https://yoast.com/404-error-pages-checking/\">Yoast&#8217;s article on website maintenance</a>.</p>\n<h3>Add/Update Important Information</h3>\n<p>It&#8217;s easy to overlook adding important information to your calendar during the holiday season because we don&#8217;t necessarily think of certain things as &#8220;events&#8221; in the traditional sense.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Special sale days and promotions</li>\n<li>Upcoming deadlines or shipping cutoffs</li>\n<li>Extended holiday hours, customer service hours, or closures outside the norm</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Want to expand your calendar beyond your own events? We&#8217;ve made it super easy to import events from other websites with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/event-aggregator/\">our new Event Aggregator service</a> that supports imports from Facebook, Meetup.com, Google calendars, iCal, ICS, and CSV.</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget to look ahead beyond the holidays while you&#8217;re adding and updating information. Once the holiday season has ended, your visitors will want to see what&#8217;s coming next on your calendar.</p>\n<h3>Prepare for More Traffic</h3>\n<p>Whether you anticipate more traffic this season or are planning ahead for your 2017 growth goals, now is the time to put scaling measures in place so your calendar can keep pace with your visitors&#8217; demands.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Clean Up Old Events</strong> &#8211; From a pure volume perspective, the more events you have, the more resources your site needs to display all of them.  That&#8217;s why periodic cleanup is important, especially if you have lots of recurring events. With <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/\">Events Calendar PRO</a>, you should periodically review your recurring events cleanup settings to see if they need any adjustments. (You can find this under Events &gt; Settings &gt; General)</li>\n<li><strong>Improve Performance</strong> &#8211; Already have loads of events on your site? You can find <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/performance-considerations/\">useful tips for improving performance &amp; load times here</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Make It Easy</strong> &#8211; Take advantage of our included filters and views to make it super easy for site visitors to find exactly what they&#8217;re looking for on your calendar. For brick &amp; mortar stores, you might want to use the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/configuring-the-this-week-widget/\">This Week widget</a> to display special holiday shopping hours. Specific views can be embedded into posts and pages using <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/embedding-calendar-views-tribe_events-shortcode/\">the [tribe_events] shortcode</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Spiff Up Your Calendar</h3>\n<p>Even if you don&#8217;t know code, you can spiff up your calendar with a few easy visual updates.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Add or Change Colors</strong> &#8211; You can change the primary colors of your calendar without needing to write CSS with our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/pro-color-customizer/\">built-in Color Customizer</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Add Images to Events</strong> &#8211; Images add major visual interest to your calendar. Besides displaying on individual event pages, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/featured-images/\">featured images</a> can be <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/adding-featured-images-to-month-view/\">added to Month View</a>, and thumbnail images can be <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/add-thumbnails-to-upcoming-events-list-widget/\">added to the upcoming events List Widget</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you do know CSS, our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/changing-fonts-and-colours/\">tutorial for basic font and color changes</a> is also a handy resource.</p>\n<h3>And Remember, We&#8217;re Here to Help</h3>\n<p>If you run into any questions as you get your events calendar ready for the holidays, hit us up on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support-forums/\">our support forums</a>. We&#8217;ll do our best to try to help you out.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/holiday-calendar-maintenance-tips/\">Holiday Calendar Maintenance Tips</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:35:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:10:{s:6:\"server\";s:5:\"nginx\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Sat, 21 Jan 2017 23:17:27 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:12:\"x-powered-by\";s:23:\"PHP/5.6.29-1~dotdeb+7.1\";s:4:\"vary\";s:6:\"Cookie\";s:4:\"etag\";s:34:\"\"6ecbc291f5a40c3586e65631193fdfa1\"\";s:12:\"x-robots-tag\";s:15:\"noindex, follow\";s:4:\"link\";s:66:\"<https://theeventscalendar.com/wp-json/>; rel=\"https://api.w.org/\"\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Sat, 21 Jan 2017 22:18:48 GMT\";s:13:\"cache-control\";s:29:\"max-age=3600, must-revalidate\";}}s:5:\"build\";s:14:\"20170118003504\";}", "no");
